# S05-T05: Mock ROOT Proposes Epics

## Objective
ROOT re-derives an epics proposal from the WHOLE chat + project context (invariant §2).

## Execution
- Implement a mock ROOT agent (`server/agents/root.mock.ts`) behind the agent interface
  from T01. Input: all `wc_messages` for the chat + a project-context blob. Output: an
  ordered epics list with `title`, `summary`, proposed `lead_role`.
- Deterministic heuristics for the demo (keyword/intent rules) — e.g. the "coffee + hungry"
  case yields ["First eat", "Make coffee"]; re-running after a new message RE-derives the
  full list (not append-only), reconciling by title against existing `wc_epics`.
- Wrap in `defineFeatureHandler('work-control', …)`; persist proposals to `wc_epics`
  (status `proposed`); emit `epic.proposed` (T09). Trigger on each new chat message.

## Out
`server/agents/root.mock.ts`, `POST /api/chat/[id]/propose-epics`

## Done when
- New chat message re-derives the epics list; proposals land in `wc_epics`.
